<h1>\{{eui-textarea}}</h1>

<div class="intro">
  A wrapper around Ember's \{{textarea}} that adds styling and error handling support.
</div>

<h2>Parameters</h2>

<ul class="parameterindex">
  <li class="header">Aesthetic</li>
  <li><a href="#section-style">style</a></li>
  <li><a href="#section-size">size</a></li>
  <li><a href="#section-width">width</a></li>
  <li><a href="#section-height">height</a></li>

  <li class="header">Error Handling</li>
  <li><a href="#section-error">error</a></li>
  <li><a href="#section-forceerrorcheck">forceErrorCheck</a></li>
</ul>


<h4 id="section-style">style <span>string</span></h4>
<p>
  Aesthetic style of the textarea.
</p>

<h5>Values</h5>
<ul class="defaults">
  <li>default (default)</li>
</ul>


<h4 id="section-size">size <span>string</span></h4>
<p>
  Controls the overall size of the textarea. Width is set via the width parameter.
</p>

<h5>Values</h5>
<ul class="defaults">
  <li>tiny</li>
  <li>small</li>
  <li>medium (default)</li>
  <li>large</li>
</ul>
<p>
  Additional sizes can be added via CSS. See {{link-to "Theming" "documentation.theming"}}
</p>

<pre>\{{#eui-textarea size='tiny'}}
  \{{textarea}}
\{{/eui-textarea}}

\{{#eui-textarea size='small'}}
  \{{textarea}}
\{{/eui-textarea}}

\{{#eui-textarea size='medium'}}
  \{{textarea}}
\{{/eui-textarea}}

\{{#eui-textarea size='large'}}
  \{{textarea}}
\{{/eui-textarea}}</pre>

<div class="output">
  {{#eui-textarea size='tiny'}}
    {{textarea}}
  {{/eui-textarea}}

  {{#eui-textarea size='small'}}
    {{textarea}}
  {{/eui-textarea}}

  {{#eui-textarea size='medium'}}
    {{textarea}}
  {{/eui-textarea}}

  {{#eui-textarea size='large'}}
    {{textarea}}
  {{/eui-textarea}}
</div>


<h4 id="section-width">width <span>string</span></h4>
<p>
  Width of the textarea. You must pass in a CSS size value with the unit. Textarea uses CSS box-sizing to ensure precentage-based sizes are actual sizes.
</p>

<pre>\{{#eui-textarea width='150px'}}
  \{{textarea placeholder='150px'}}
\{{/eui-textarea}}

\{{#eui-textarea width='15em'}}
  \{{textarea placeholder='15em'}}
\{{/eui-textarea}}

\{{#eui-textarea width='30%'}}
  \{{textarea placeholder='30%'}}
\{{/eui-textarea}}</pre>

<div class="output">
  {{#eui-textarea width='150px'}}
    {{textarea placeholder='150px'}}
  {{/eui-textarea}}

  {{#eui-textarea width='15em'}}
    {{textarea placeholder='15em'}}
  {{/eui-textarea}}

  {{#eui-textarea width='30%'}}
    {{textarea placeholder='30%'}}
  {{/eui-textarea}}
</div>


<h4 id="section-height">height <span>string</span></h4>
<p>
  Height of the textarea. You must pass in a CSS size value with the unit. Textarea uses CSS box-sizing to ensure precentage-based sizes are actual sizes.
</p>

<pre>\{{#eui-textarea height='50px'}}
  \{{textarea placeholder='50px'}}
\{{/eui-textarea}}

\{{#eui-textarea height='5em'}}
  \{{textarea placeholder='5em'}}
\{{/eui-textarea}}</pre>

<div class="output">
  {{#eui-textarea height='50px'}}
    {{textarea placeholder='50px'}}
  {{/eui-textarea}}

  {{#eui-textarea height='5em'}}
    {{textarea placeholder='5em'}}
  {{/eui-textarea}}
</div>


<h4 id="section-error">error <span>boolean | string</span></h4>
<p>
  Responsible for validation and error handling. See {{link-to "Error Handling" "documentation.errorhandling"}}
</p>


<h4 id="section-forceerrorcheck">forceErrorCheck <span>boolean</span></h4>
<p>
  If set to <em>true</em> the textarea will force an error check, even if the value is blank.
</p>
